args: The history between Askr and Embla\nis complicated to say the least.
The former emperor of Embla sought\nto bring prosperity to his country by\nenslaving Heroes, as well as Askr itself.

Several years ago, Princess Veronica
suddenly declared her intention to follow
in her father's footsteps and commenced
a new invasion of Askr.
My sister once said she might have\ndone it because she was lonely,\nbut I don't know the truth of it.
Thank you for telling me all of that.\nI actually think your sister might\nnot be too far off the mark.
Yes, she tried to kill those soldiers, but she\ndoesn't strike me as a bad person, per se.
I think she just doesn't know\nhow to make friends.
Many of us have long suspected the same.
I fear something ill may have occurred.\nCome, Prince! We must make haste!
I came to Veronica's room in the vain\nhope of finally cleaning it and found\nher lying motionless on the floor.
Well, she's still breathin' at least.\n...Heeey! Can you heeeear me?!
I'm glad to hear that. But what possessed\nyou to starve yourself for so long?
No one brought food to my room.
What?! Wait, no. Needs more surprise.\n...WHAAAAT?!
Food always appears in my room at home.\nIt never did here.
Eventually, I was too hungry to move.
Ah, I get it. Back in Embla, you have\nservants who bring you food.

*sigh* I thought I was being considerate
by leaving her alone to her own devices,
but if I had gone in earlier, none of this
would have happened.
Please do not blame yourself, Cleo.\nIf Princess Veronica was hungry,\nshe had but to tell us so.
It's all right to rely on us, Princess,\njust as you did during the time\nwhen you lost your memory.
No. We're not fighting now, but I won't owe\nanything to the prince of another country.

There are all kinds of people here in this
castle, from lots of different classes and
backgrounds. But even so, we all have
one thing in common...
I'm not a prince or a title.\nI am {player_name},\njust as you're Veronica.
Why would you choose not to be a prince?\nThat's strange. You're strange.
Stranger than any of the Heroes\nI've met from other worlds.
Oh, he's a strange one, all right.
But he's just tryin' to tell you it's okay\nto be free and live life how you want.

That might've been hard to do back home,
but so long as you're in our world, just put
all that royalty stuff out of your head and
try to be our friend!
That's what I want, anyway! You're kinda\nlike a little sister I want to help out.
Is there anyone normal in this castle?
I am with them in this, Princess Veronica.
This is neither Askr nor Embla.\nAnd until we find a way back home,\nwe're all after the same thing.
All right. I'll try to be...friends.\nBut only since it's temporary.
Hot damn! Let's shake on it!
Ow. Let go. You're hurting me.
Ack! Sorry! I did it the same way I shake\nhands with my sister, and she's kind of\na beast. ...How's this?
You're strange AND naive.\nWhat a troublesome bunch.
But a promise is a promise.\nI'll keep it.
That's what my brother once taught me...
